[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### Walkthrough
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 1: Ingest vital sign records into the stream.** The pipeline starts at the device gateway. Bedside monitors emit HL7 v2 ORU-R01 messages (or proprietary device API events); the interface engine translates them to canonical JSON records and writes them to Kinesis. Flowsheet entries from the EHR arrive as FHIR Observation resources via webhook or polling and are normalized into the same schema. Each record carries patient ID, signal type, timestamp, value, unit, source, and any device-reported quality indicators. Skipping this normalization is the most common source of bugs downstream because every monitor vendor has slightly different field names and unit conventions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION ingest_vital_record(raw_message):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Translate the raw input (HL7 v2 ORU, FHIR Observation, or vendor JSON)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // into a canonical record. The translation table is per-source because
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // different monitors call the same vital sign different things.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     canonical = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id:        extract_patient_id(raw_message),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         signal_type:       map_to_canonical_signal(raw_message.observation_code),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         timestamp:         parse_timestamp(raw_message.collection_ts),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         value:             extract_numeric_value(raw_message),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         unit:              map_to_canonical_unit(raw_message.unit, signal_type),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         source:            raw_message.source_id,             // monitor vendor / device id
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         location:          raw_message.bed_or_unit,           // unit + bed for routing
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         quality_flags:     extract_device_quality_flags(raw_message),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         encounter_class:   raw_message.encounter_class        // ambulatory / inpatient / icu
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Reject records that fail basic validation. Better to drop a malformed
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // record than to inject bad data into the streaming pipeline. Quarantine
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // failures to S3 for offline review.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IF canonical.patient_id is null OR canonical.value is null OR canonical.timestamp is null:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         write raw_message to s3://raw-vitals/quarantine/
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         log warning "rejected record"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         RETURN null
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Write to Kinesis, partitioned by patient_id so all of a patient's
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // records land on the same shard. This is essential for keyed-state
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // processing in Flink downstream.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     write canonical to kinesis_stream "vital-signs-stream" with partition_key = canonical.patient_id
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Also archive to S3 for long-term retention, retraining, and audit.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     write canonical to s3://raw-vitals/dt=YYYY-MM-DD/unit=LOC/
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN canonical
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 2: Filter artifacts in the streaming application.** Inside the Managed Flink application, each incoming record passes through an artifact filter before reaching the baseline and scoring stages. The filter combines device-reported quality flags, physiological plausibility checks, and short-window stability. Records that pass continue downstream; records that fail are tagged and dropped from the trajectory pipeline (but retained in raw archive for review). Skipping this step lets artifact masquerade as deterioration and floods the alert layer.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION artifact_filter(record, recent_window):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Device-reported quality. Most modern monitors flag low-quality
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // measurements explicitly. Trust those flags as the first cut.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IF record.quality_flags contains ("low_signal_quality", "lead_off", "sensor_disconnect", "motion"):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         emit_metric("artifact.device_flagged", 1, dimensions = (signal_type))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         RETURN { passes: false, reason: "device_quality" }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Physiological plausibility. Each signal has a range outside which
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // the value is impossible (heart rate of 300 BPM, SpO2 of 50%, etc.).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     plausible_range = lookup_plausibility_bounds(record.signal_type)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IF record.value < plausible_range.min OR record.value > plausible_range.max:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         emit_metric("artifact.implausible_value", 1, dimensions = (signal_type))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         RETURN { passes: false, reason: "implausible" }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Short-window stability. A single value far outside the recent
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // distribution flanked by normal values is suspicious. Compute the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // recent median and median absolute deviation (MAD), and flag any
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // value more than N MADs from the median when the surrounding values
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // are stable.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     recent_values = filter recent_window where signal_type = record.signal_type
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IF count(recent_values) >= 5:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         recent_median = median(recent_values)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         recent_mad    = median_absolute_deviation(recent_values)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         deviation     = abs(record.value - recent_median) / max(recent_mad, minimum_mad_floor)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         IF deviation > stability_threshold AND not_consistent_with_neighbors(record, recent_window):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             emit_metric("artifact.unstable_outlier", 1, dimensions = (signal_type))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             RETURN { passes: false, reason: "unstable_outlier" }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Sustained no-data check. If the last N minutes for this signal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // have no clean records, the system should not invent a baseline
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // from old data. Flag the patient_id+signal_type as "no_data" until
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // fresh measurements arrive.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     update_data_freshness(record.patient_id, record.signal_type, record.timestamp)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN { passes: true }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 3: Maintain per-patient baselines in keyed state.** The Flink application uses keyed state per (patient_id, signal_type). For each patient and each vital sign, it maintains two rolling baselines: a short-window (4-hour) and a long-window (24-hour) computed from clean, stable measurements. The baselines update with each clean measurement. Acute interventions and known activity events can mark a measurement as "non-baseline" so the patient's baseline stays anchored to the truly stable periods. This step is where most of the value of patient-specific reasoning lives.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION update_baseline_state(patient_id, signal_type, clean_record, current_state):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Append the clean record to the short-window buffer. Drop records
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // outside the 4-hour window.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     short_window = filter current_state.short_window
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                    where timestamp > now() - 4 hours
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     short_window = append short_window with clean_record
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Append the clean record to the long-window buffer. Drop records
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // outside the 24-hour window.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     long_window = filter current_state.long_window
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                   where timestamp > now() - 24 hours
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     long_window = append long_window with clean_record
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Need a minimum number of stable measurements before the baseline
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // is considered ready. For continuously monitored signals, 30
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // clean measurements over the last 4 hours is a reasonable floor.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     minimum_sample_count = lookup_minimum_for_signal(signal_type)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IF count(short_window) >= minimum_sample_count:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Use a robust statistic to resist any artifact that slipped through.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         baseline_short_value = trimmed_mean(short_window.values, trim_percent = 10)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         baseline_short_dispersion = mad(short_window.values)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ELSE:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         baseline_short_value = null
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IF count(long_window) >= minimum_sample_count * 4:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         baseline_long_value = trimmed_mean(long_window.values, trim_percent = 10)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         baseline_long_dispersion = mad(long_window.values)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ELSE:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         baseline_long_value = null
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     new_state = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id:                patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         signal_type:               signal_type,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         short_window:              short_window,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         long_window:               long_window,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         baseline_short_value:      baseline_short_value,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         baseline_short_dispersion: baseline_short_dispersion,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         baseline_long_value:       baseline_long_value,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         baseline_long_dispersion:  baseline_long_dispersion,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         last_update_ts:            now()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     persist new_state to flink_keyed_state
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Also write a snapshot to DynamoDB for downstream lookups by Lambda.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     write_to_dynamodb("patient-state", patient_id, new_state)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN new_state
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 4: Compute the multi-parameter deterioration score.** Each clean measurement triggers a recalculation of the patient's overall deterioration score using all of their recent vital signs. NEWS2 is the standard default: each vital sign contributes 0 to 3 points based on its current value, and the points are summed. A score of 0 to 4 is normal-low risk, 5 to 6 is medium risk (escalate to a senior nurse), and 7 or higher is high risk (escalate to a rapid response). The pseudocode below is NEWS2-shaped; production systems may run a more sophisticated joint model in parallel as a second opinion.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION compute_news2_score(patient_id, current_vitals):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Pull the most recent value for each component vital sign.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     rr     = current_vitals.respiratory_rate                    // breaths per minute
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     spo2   = current_vitals.oxygen_saturation                   // percent
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     on_o2  = current_vitals.supplemental_oxygen_in_use          // boolean
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     temp   = current_vitals.temperature                         // celsius
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sbp    = current_vitals.systolic_blood_pressure             // mmHg
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     hr     = current_vitals.heart_rate                          // beats per minute
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     consc  = current_vitals.consciousness_level                 // ACVPU: alert, confusion, voice, pain, unresponsive
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Score each component using the NEWS2 thresholds.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // (See https://www.rcp.ac.uk/improving-care/national-early-warning-score-news-2/
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // for the official chart.)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     rr_points    = score_rr_news2(rr)            // 0 to 3 points
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     spo2_points  = score_spo2_news2(spo2)        // 0 to 3 points
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     o2_points    = score_o2_news2(on_o2)         // 0 or 2 points
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     temp_points  = score_temp_news2(temp)        // 0 to 3 points
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sbp_points   = score_sbp_news2(sbp)          // 0 to 3 points
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     hr_points    = score_hr_news2(hr)            // 0 to 3 points
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     consc_points = score_consc_news2(consc)      // 0 or 3 points
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     total_score = rr_points + spo2_points + o2_points + temp_points
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                   + sbp_points + hr_points + consc_points
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Identify the highest single-parameter contributor. NEWS2 escalation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // rules also fire on any single 3-point parameter, so we capture this
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // for the relevance layer.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     component_breakdown = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         respiratory_rate:    rr_points,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         oxygen_saturation:   spo2_points,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         supplemental_oxygen: o2_points,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         temperature:         temp_points,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         systolic_bp:         sbp_points,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         heart_rate:          hr_points,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         consciousness:       consc_points
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     highest_single_param = max(component_breakdown.values())
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     score_record = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id:           patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         score_ts:             now(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         news2_total:          total_score,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         component_breakdown:  component_breakdown,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         highest_single_param: highest_single_param
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Optionally call the joint deterioration model as a second opinion.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IF joint_model_enabled_for_unit(current_vitals.unit):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         score_record.joint_model_score = sagemaker_invoke_endpoint(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             endpoint_name = "deterioration-model",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             features      = build_feature_vector(patient_id, current_vitals)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     write score_record to timestream "vitals-and-scores"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     write_to_dynamodb("patient-state", patient_id, latest_score = score_record)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN score_record
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 5: Detect trajectory changes in the score.** Given the time series of score values, the trajectory detector flags meaningful changes. A common production pattern combines a sliding-window slope test (the score is rising significantly over the last hour) with a CUSUM test (the score has been accumulating positive deviations from baseline for long enough to matter). Requiring both methods to fire reduces false alarms compared to relying on either alone.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION detect_trajectory_change(patient_id, score_history):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Pull the recent score series (60 minutes is a typical default for
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // continuous monitoring; adjust for intermittent capture).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     recent_scores = filter score_history where ts > now() - 60 minutes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Need at least 5 score points to run any meaningful detector.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IF count(recent_scores) < 5:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         RETURN { trajectory_status: "insufficient_data" }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Detector 1: sliding-window slope. Fit a linear regression to the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // recent scores against time and test whether the slope is significantly
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // positive. Use a non-parametric alternative (Theil-Sen) if the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // distribution is heavy-tailed.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     slope, slope_p_value = linear_regression_slope(recent_scores)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Detector 2: CUSUM. Track the cumulative sum of (score - baseline_score)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // since the last reset. Trip when the cumulative sum exceeds a calibrated
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // threshold (typically expressed in units of MAD).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     cusum_state = update_cusum_state(patient_id, recent_scores, baseline_score)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     cusum_tripped = cusum_state.cumulative_deviation > cusum_threshold
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Detector 3 (optional): EWMA. Useful as a sustained-shift detector.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ewma_value = update_ewma(patient_id, recent_scores, lambda = 0.2)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ewma_tripped = ewma_value > baseline_score + ewma_control_limit
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    425[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    426[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Production rule: require slope detector AND CUSUM to fire (or
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    427[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // any single detector AND a high single-parameter NEWS2 component
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    428[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // of 3). This composite reduces false alarms substantially.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    429[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     primary_trigger = (slope > minimum_slope AND slope_p_value < 0.05) AND cusum_tripped
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    430[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     secondary_trigger = highest_single_param_score >= 3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    431[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    432[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IF primary_trigger OR secondary_trigger:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    433[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         trajectory_event = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    434[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             patient_id:               patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    435[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             event_ts:                 now(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    436[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             current_score:            most_recent(recent_scores).value,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    437[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             score_slope_per_minute:   slope,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    438[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             cumulative_deviation:     cusum_state.cumulative_deviation,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    439[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             highest_single_param:     highest_single_param_score,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    440[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             recent_score_series:      recent_scores,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    441[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             triggers_fired:           list_of_active_triggers
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    442[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    443[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         emit trajectory_event to "trajectory-events" lambda
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    444[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         RETURN trajectory_event
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    445[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    446[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN { trajectory_status: "stable" }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    447[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    448[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    449[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 6: Apply clinical relevance rules and deliver the alert.** Trajectory events flow to a Lambda function that applies the clinical relevance rules: minimum sustained duration, suppression for known events (post-procedure recovery, recent ambulation, recent medication that produces the trajectory), unit-specific routing, and acuity-aware prioritization. Events that pass the relevance layer become surfaced alerts; events that fail are logged for tuning the rules. Routing decides which surface receives the alert (charge nurse, RRT pager, EHR deterioration column, or all of the above).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    450[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    451[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    452[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION apply_clinical_relevance(trajectory_event):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    453[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     patient_context = lookup_patient_context(trajectory_event.patient_id)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    454[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Patient context includes: assigned unit, attending physician, recent
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    455[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // medications (vasoactives, beta-blockers, sedatives that change vitals
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    456[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // expectedly), recent procedures, current isolation status, code status,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    457[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // and any active suppression flags from prior alerts in the last hour.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    458[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    459[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Sustained duration check. The trajectory must have been elevated for
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    460[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // at least the configured minimum (typically 15 minutes of continuous
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    461[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // elevation for med-surg, 5 minutes for ICU step-down).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    462[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     duration_pass = trajectory_event.elevated_duration_minutes >=
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    463[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     rules.minimum_duration_for_unit(patient_context.unit_type)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    464[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    465[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Recent intervention suppression. If the patient just received a
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    466[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // medication or intervention that explains the trajectory, suppress.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    467[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     intervention_suppression = check_recent_interventions(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    468[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id = trajectory_event.patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    469[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         within     = 30 minutes,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    470[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         explains_trajectory = trajectory_event.signal_pattern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    471[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    472[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    473[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Active alert suppression. If the same patient already has an active
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    474[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // surfaced alert in the last hour, do not page again unless the score
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    475[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // has worsened by at least N points.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    476[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     active_alert_suppression = check_active_alerts(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    477[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         patient_id        = trajectory_event.patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    478[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         within            = 60 minutes,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    479[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         worsening_required = active_alert_worsening_threshold
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    480[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    481[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    482[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Compose the routing decision. NEWS2 of 5 to 6 routes to charge nurse;
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    483[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // NEWS2 of 7+ or single-parameter 3+ routes to rapid response team;
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    484[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // a sustained-but-modest trajectory routes to the EHR deterioration column
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    485[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // without paging.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    486[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     routing = decide_routing(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    487[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         score                = trajectory_event.current_score,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         highest_single_param = trajectory_event.highest_single_param,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         unit_type            = patient_context.unit_type,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         time_of_day          = now().hour
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    491[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    492[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     surface = duration_pass AND NOT intervention_suppression AND NOT active_alert_suppression
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IF surface:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    496[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         alert_payload = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    497[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             patient_id:           trajectory_event.patient_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             alert_id:             generate_uuid(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    499[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             alert_ts:             now(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    500[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             severity:             map_score_to_severity(trajectory_event.current_score),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    501[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             news2_score:          trajectory_event.current_score,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    502[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             score_components:     trajectory_event.component_breakdown,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    503[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             score_trajectory:     trajectory_event.recent_score_series,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    504[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             elevated_duration:    trajectory_event.elevated_duration_minutes,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    505[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             triggering_signals:   identify_top_contributors(trajectory_event),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    506[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             patient_location:     patient_context.unit + " bed " + patient_context.bed,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    507[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             routing_targets:      routing.targets,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    508[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             explanation_text:     compose_clinical_explanation(trajectory_event, patient_context),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    509[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             recommended_action:   map_score_to_action(trajectory_event.current_score),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             model_version:        rules.version
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         write alert_payload to dynamodb "active-alerts"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         FOR target in routing.targets:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             IF target == "rrt_pager":     publish to sns_topic "rrt-page" with alert_payload
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             IF target == "charge_nurse":  publish to sns_topic "charge-nurse-alert" with alert_payload
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             IF target == "ehr_di_column": update_ehr_di_column(alert_payload)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         emit_cloudwatch_metric("alerts.surfaced", 1,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                                 dimensions = (unit, severity))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         RETURN { surfaced: true, alert_id: alert_payload.alert_id }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     write_to_s3("suppressed-trajectories/", trajectory_event, suppression_reason)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     emit_cloudwatch_metric("alerts.suppressed", 1, dimensions = (unit, suppression_reason))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN { surfaced: false, suppression_reason: suppression_reason }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > **Curious how this looks in Python?** The pseudocode above covers the concepts. If you'd like to see sample Python code that demonstrates these patterns using boto3, statsmodels, and a streaming-style Python implementation, check out the [Python Example](chapter12.07-python-example). It walks through each step with inline comments and notes on what you'd need to change for a real deployment.
